Part 27 [2024/04/19 12:00:00 GMT+0000] 
[00:56:43] Participant 6: No ID, but able to confirm victim's identity, secured scene. Made initial search of area, no signs of struggle on riverbank. Fall from the ledge seems likely. Oh yeah, coroner arrived – why didn't we read this – coroner arrived, agreed fall is likely cause of death. Says he's probably been dead three, four hours. 
[00:57:03] Participant 5: So, he did die between this, 2.04, and… [00:57:11] Participant 6: I guess, yeah. Went to talk to neighbour who found body. Stated she was out for a walk shortly after six, when she discovered the body on the rocks beside the waterfall, then returned home to call police. Okay, ten o'clock, back to scene, search of water underway. Haven't found much so far, besides some empty beer bottles, probably just litter, beer bottles. Gave up day to McGinty, he agrees with accident scenario, will proceed accordingly. Coroner okayed removal of remains mortis, Bob's Funeral Home to pick up. Told Cherie, she took it about as expected. Did my best to calm her down. Reassured her, foul play was unlikely. Made sure she called her mother to come down, and stay, so she's not alone at a time like this. So, I guess the Deputy did not do it. Maybe she did it, like, maybe Cherie did it. 
[00:58:23] Participant 5: I think so. Because, so this was posted on 6.32 a.m., the body was discovered at 6.37. 
[00:58:28] Participant 6: Yeah. [00:58:30] Participant 5: And the sound, like, the knocking, the songs, and everything, was for a couple of hours. 
[00:58:30] Participant 6: And this one says, that's what all the noise was around 2.30 last night. So, I think she showed up, like, at 2.30, maybe. [00:58:54] Participant 5: Yeah. [00:58:54] Participant 6: Uh-huh. Well… [00:58:54] Participant 5: But there is no, like, possibility that she was in there, she got some, like, sounds, and just put songs for hours, and hours. 
[00:59:14] Participant 6: Yeah, she doesn't have an alibi. What's the things we need to be, like, motive, means, and, motive, something else, and something, I forgot? 
[00:59:26] Participant 5: Was it… [00:59:27] Participant 4: Means, motive, and… 
[00:59:30] Participant 6: Opportunity? 
[00:59:30] Participant 4: …yeah. [00:59:30] Participant 6: But it means… 
[00:59:30] Participant 5: It says here. [00:59:31] Participant 4: So, means is how they did it, I assume, or she just pushed him off the cliff. 
[00:59:45] Participant 6: Yeah, means, motive, and opportunity. So… 
[00:59:47] Participant 5: So, we have the means. I know the motive, she wanted to stay with Chris. 
[00:59:51] Participant 6: Yeah. [00:59:52] Participant 4: I think a motive is different. I think a motive is to either get him out the picture to sell the land… 
[00:59:59] Participant 5: But I don't think she'll get anything. So, she's not sure she'll get something, because I think the will was, like, revised after November 23rd. [01:00:20] Participant 6: Yeah, but she doesn't know that.
